responses.answer: Prognosis is predicted and evaluated by a speech language pathologist.
Multiple regression analysis can be applied to study the impact of child's gender, television viewing time, and interaction time with mother on child's expressive language development.
Language learning disabilities are characterized by difficulties in reading and writing and can co-occur with autism spectrum disorder.
Maintenance phase is part of fluency shaping therapy, which adults who stutter undergo; specific activities in maintenance phase are not detailed in the data.
Processing nonLiteral language is most prominently impaired in patients with right hemisphere damage.
